## Notifications

Use `terminal-notifier` (macOS) for alerts:

```bash
terminal-notifier \
  -title "Claude" \
  -subtitle "Weekly Reflection Ready" \
  -message "3 themes surfaced, 2 tensions" \
  -sound default \
  -group "claude-reflections"
```

**Parameters:**
- `-title` — Always "Claude"
- `-subtitle` — Workflow or alert type
- `-message` — Terse summary (1 line)
- `-group` — Group ID to prevent notification spam

**By urgency:**
- 🔴 Urgent: Sound + open file on click (`-open "file://..."`)
- 🟡 Normal: Sound, no auto-open
- 🟢 FYI: No sound (`-sound ""`)

Linux users: substitute `notify-send` or comparable.

